This is the second most called `simp` lemma and never succeeds (see [Zulip](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Infrastructure.20for.20tracking.20frequently.20applied.20simp.20theorems/near/459926416)]. It's also way too specific to be reasonably useful outside of the file itself.

Also did some pretty minor cleanup.

Instead of unsimping, do you mind changing the statement to either
```suggestion
theorem iSup_iterate_eq_nfp (f : Ordinal.{u} ‚Üí Ordinal.{u}) : ‚®Ü n, f^[n] = nfp f := by
```
or
```suggestion
theorem iSup_iterate_eq_nfp (f : Ordinal.{u} ‚Üí Ordinal.{u}) (a : Ordinal.{u}) :
    ‚®Ü n, f^[n] a = nfp f a := by
```
? Possibly we want both
The first one is definitely better, though I still don't think it's justified in being a simp lemma. Surely the second theorem is an immediate consequence of rewriting the first, right?

> I still don't think it's justified in being a simp lemma

I don't mind it not being simp, but at least it won't be a performance penalty since it will be keyed on (the rather uncommon) `Ordinal.sup`.

> Surely the second theorem is an immediate consequence of rewriting the first, right?

It is, but I can imagine you might want to rewrite an expression where eg both `nfp f a` and `nfp f b` appear, and you might not want to rewrite both. Or maybe you want to rewrite it backwards, in which case it's annoying having to call `iSup_apply` explicitly.

I should note that theorems of ordinals are written with `Ordinal.sup` instead of its synonym `iSup`. This is a much-needed refactor that just hasn't been done.

Also, `‚®Ü n, f^[n]` isn't the correct term, as the supremum of functions `Ordinal ‚Üí Ordinal` isn't defined.
I've replaced the funext version of `sup_iterate_eq_nfp ` by the applied version. It doesn't seem like the original was all that useful.

> `‚®Ü n, f^[n]` isn't the correct term, as the supremum of functions `Ordinal ‚Üí Ordinal` isn't defined.

Well, it is, by taking pointwise sups: https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/CompleteLattice.html#iSup_apply
Oh, that's nice. Even more reason to do that refactor.
